Posts.Content:
I have what they call heterogeneously dense breasts and always have to go back- always!! Even with digital Mammos. Heck they did a call back with an MRI with contrast.
It's scary as heck on its own, but having so recent a loss I cannot imagine what you are feeling.
I will tell you this, most times....most...it's calcium deposits....also called PASH...or Fibroid growths...
If you are unsure make them do a biopsy because that is what I was told to do.
Good luck!!
Dxed at 13, from a TBI in the late 70's (over 30 yrs on meds)
Just made 15 yr grand mal free
Posts.Title: Digital mamma call back - freaking out
